  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SOC Analyst",
  "description": "<h3><u><strong>Your missions:</strong></u></h3><p>Within our Singapore and Montréal (Canada) agency, you will join the XtendedSOC team as a Senior Analyst to strengthen the existing setup, bringing your knowledge and experience in incident response. Your responsibilities will include :</p><p><strong>Participate in building the service:</strong></p><p>- Take charge of XDR and SIEM technical solutions (from an administration and operational perspective);</p><p>- Test and develop processes related to tools and service operations.</p><p>- Monitor alerts and incidents on a 24/7 basis</p><p>- Develop connectors to interface detection solutions with our internal tools.</p><p><strong>Operate the service:</strong></p><p>- Conduct proactive prevention with clients.</p><p>- Handle security alerts from detection solutions.</p><p>- Qualify, analyze, and notify clients of potential security incidents.</p><p>- Maintain the functionality of detection solutions.</p><p>- Implement EDR,XDR,SIEM solutions along customer technical team</p><p>- Improve detection quality for clients.</p><p>- Guide client technical teams regarding mitigations and corrective actions to implement, ensuring the security of the company's IT system.</p><p>- Ensure continuous monitoring, focusing on threats as well as software and hardware vulnerabilities.</p><p><strong>Contribute to service improvement:</strong></p><p>- Identify possible enhancements (tools, monitoring, processes) to improve service quality and/or efficiency.</p><p>- Study how to integrate frameworks (MITRE, ETSI) into our detection coverage.</p><p>- Document knowledge bases and processing procedures.</p><p></p><h3><u><strong>Your strengths and key skills for the position :</strong></u></h3><p>You hold a Bac+4/5 degree from an engineering school or a university in the field of computer science, information systems, or ideally Cybersecurity.</p><p>You have over 3 years of experience in a similar position.</p><p>You are dynamic, have developed a certain level of autonomy in your tasks, aspire to work in a friendly and team-oriented environment, and enjoy interacting with clients, even in crisis situations.</p><p>You are organized, comfortable both orally and in writing, and you are creative and curious about IT and cybersecurity topics. Proficiency in both English and French is essential, as the role requires frequent collaboration with international clients and internal stakeholders, many of whom communicate primarily in French or English, across the Orange Cyberdefense network. This includes contributing to incident response and threat analysis for major French and global clients.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
